

# ===
# build:    Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies (example scopes: gulp, broccoli, npm)
# ci:       Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts (example scopes: Travis, Circle, BrowserStack, SauceLabs)
# docs:     Documentation only changes
# feat:     A new feature
# fix:      A bug fix
# perf:     A code change that improves performance
# refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# style:    Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (white-space, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc)
# test:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
# chore: Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools and libraries such as documentation generation

# ==== Emojis ====
# ✨  :sparkles:          機能追加
# 💄  :lipstick:          UI/UX/デザイン
# ❤️   :heart:             バグ修正
# ✅  :white_check_mark:  テスト追加
# 🎉  :tada:              盛大に祝うべき大きな機能追加
# 💬  :speech_balloon:    コメント
# ♻️   :recycle:           リファクタリング
# 📝  :memo:              ドキュメントの編集
# 🚀  :rocket:            デプロイ
# ⚡  :zap:               パフォーマンス
# 🚱  :non-potable_water: メモリリーク修正
# 👕  :shirt:             Lintエラーの修正やコードスタイルの修正
# 👮  :cop:               セキュリティ関連の改善
# ⚙   :gear:              設定の追加
# 📦  :package:           パッケージの更新
# ➕  :heavy_plus_sign:   依存性の追加
# ➖  :heavy_minus_sign:  依存性の削除
# ⬆️   :arrow_up:          ライブラリのアップグレード
# ⬇️   :arrow_down:        ライブラリのダウングレード
# 💚  :green_heart:       CIの修正・改善
# 🐳  :whale:             Docker
# 💥  :boom:              破壊的変更
# 🔥  :fire:              削除
# 🚿  :shower:            不要な機能・使われなくなった機能の削除
# 🚚  :truck:             移動
# 🚧  :construction:      W.I.P.

# ==== Format ====
# :emoji: Subject
#
# Commit body...

# ==== The Seven Rules ====
# 1. Separate subject from body with a blank line
# 2. Limit the subject line to 50 characters
# 3. Capitalize the subject line
# 4. Do not end the subject line with a period
# 5. Use the imperative mood in the subject line
# 6. Wrap the body at 72 characters
# 7. Use the body to explain what and why vs. how
#
# How to Write a Git Commit Message http://chris.beams.io/posts/git-commit/

# for http://memo.goodpatch.co/2016/07/beautiful-commits-with-emojis/
